translation.text: Airport & South Line, Bankstown Line, Blue Mountains Line, Central Coast & Newcastle Line, Cumberland Line, Inner West & Leppington Line, Olympic Park, Western Line - Major delays

Blue Mountains Line, Inner West & Leppington Line, Olympic Park, Western Line - Partial Closure

due to a fatality at Lidcombe. No trains are running between Strathfield and Parramatta in both directions. A very limited number of replacement buses are beginning to arrive at some stations; however, these are delayed due to heavy traffic. 

Major delays continue between Strathfield and Central in both directions, as a result. T9 Northern Line services are beginning to run between Strathfield and Central, stopping additionally at Croydon and Ashfield towards the City, and Stanmore, Summer Hill, Ashfield and Croydon away from the City. You may wish to make alternative travel arrangements to Strathfield, where you can change for a T9 Northern Line train service towards the City. Please continue to avoid all non-essential travel, as delays are expected to be extensive and ongoing.

If you do need to travel, please allow plenty of additional travel time, listen to announcements, check information screens and transport apps, as stopping patterns and departure platforms may change at short notice.

Central Coast & Newcastle Line, Northern Line - Delays

Trains have now resumed running between Strathfield and Central. Delays can still be expected due to a fatality at Lidcombe. Please continue allow plenty of extra travel time and check station information screens and transport apps and listen to announcements for updates.

If you are travelling from Museum, St James, Circular Quay, Wynyard or Town Hall to stations on the Richmond Line and have limited mobility, please board a T1 Western Line service heading towards Penrith/Emu Plains and change at Seven Hills. If you are at Central you can board a direct service to Richmond from platforms 1-12.

Station Update - Artarmon, Auburn, Ashfield and more

Due to a fatality at Lidcombe some services are currently experiencing major flow on delays. Some stopping patterns and platform may change at short notice. Customers are advised to listen to announcements, check information screens and transport apps before boarding services.

There are changes happening at Central Station during Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may be limited, which means using different stairs, escalators and lifts. 

Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. 

For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6049959
Due to station redevelopment work some platforms have reduced capacity. Please avoid standing in front of construction zones and remain behind the yellow line on the platform.

There are changes at Sydenham station during Sydney Metro construction.

T3 Bankstown Line services to the City are available from platform 3 and to Lidcombe and Liverpool from platform 4.

A new Metro concourse is also being constructed at the Northern end of the station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5.

If you need help, please see staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info
